    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Compound of sulfur and manganese. It occurs naturally as the mineral alabandite. It may be synthesized by reacting ammonium sulfide with a manganese salt. Compound of sulfur and manganese. It occurs naturally as the mineral alabandite. It may be synthesized by reacting ammonium sulfide with a manganese salt. Found as in inclusion in cast iron to which it has been added to aid in solidification.</Note_Text>
